The first issue of Now, a quarterly comics anthology from Fantagraphics, begins with a text page that falls just shy of manifesto territory. It&rsquo;s by Now editor Eric Reynolds, and it argues that &ldquo;The anthology format can be an inherent force for good.&rdquo;
Reynolds makes a compelling argument. Anthologies are a great way for young cartoonists to get exposure and to experiment with styles without committing to a longform project.

